text: The Honor Guard or native name Kebur Zabagna (Amharic; ክብር ዘበኛ) is a guard unit equivalent to Imperial Guard. This Guard unit was created in 1917 under Empress Zewditu I and ended at the last Emperor of Ethiopia resigned in 1974.
